The German government wants to impose
a salary cap of 500,000 euros ($687,100) on employees of banks
that received state aid, the  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  newspaper
reported, citing an interview with Deputy Finance Minister
 Hartmut Koschyk .  The Justice Ministry is currently examining whether it can
legally implement binding pay caps, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ragnhild Kjetland  in Frankfurt at 
 rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Vidya Root at
